{"article_id":"O3VTxfLTn026Es3A","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Time was when Barack Obama , an instructor of constitutional law at the University of Chicago , was skeptical of American presidents ' aggressive use of executive power .","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"In 2008 , as a candidate for president , Senator Obama railed against President George W. Bush ' s penchant","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"for circumventing Congress .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Now , seven years into his own presidency , Obama is a master at executive action ,","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"pushing the envelope time and again","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"when Congress won ' t act","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"- even after saying","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"he ' s done everything","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"he can .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"Gun control is his latest mission ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"with new actions to be announced Tuesday , a televised town hall on the subject Thursday night ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"and gun violence expected to be a focus again in next week 's State of the Union address .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"One new measure would tighten the so-called \" gun-show loophole ''","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"by requiring occasional gun dealers","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"- such as those","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"who sell at gun shows and over the Internet -","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"to obtain licenses","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"and conduct background checks on buyers .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"In remarks to reporters Monday evening , administration officials also laid out plans","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"to boost enforcement of federal gun laws ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"including the hiring of additional FBI personnel","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"to process background checks .","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"Some of Obama ' s new gun measures ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"including an additional $ 500 million in federal funds","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to increase access to mental health care ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"require congressional approval .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"But those","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"enacted by executive order","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"have the force of law","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"- though they can be undone by the next president .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"And therein lies the rub for Obama :","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"If he is replaced by a Republican ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"he is sure to see a raft of measures eliminated with a quick signature , on matters","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"ranging from gun control to immigration to women ' s reproductive health .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"The large Republican presidential field has uniformly decried Obama ' s aggressive use of executive power .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"On Saturday , front-runner Donald Trump vowed to \" unsign \" any gun control measures","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Obama enacts unilaterally .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"\" So he 's going to sign another executive order","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"having to do with the Second Amendment ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"having to do with guns , \"","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"Mr. Trump told a rally in Biloxi , Miss .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"\" I will veto .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"I will unsign that so fast . ''","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"On Monday , Texas Sen. Ted Cruz","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"- a Harvard-trained lawyer","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"who has argued cases before the Supreme Court -","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"promised on day one as president to `` rescind every single illegal and unconstitutional executive action '' by Obama .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"New Jersey Gov . Chris Christie , a former US attorney , called Obama a \" petulant child \" and a \" dictator \" over his planned actions on guns .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"But the reality is that , whoever the next president is","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"- the most conservative Republican or the most liberal Democrat -","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"he or she is likely to follow his lead on use of executive authority .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"\" I suspect","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that everybody","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"running for president","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"will be aggressive in that light , \"","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"says Henry Barbour , Republican national committeeman from Mississippi .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Even if the Republicans sweep the 2016 elections in November","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"- winning the White House","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"and keeping control of both houses of Congress -","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"the Democrats will still be able to block legislation","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"they don ' t like","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"through the filibuster , or endless debate ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"which requires 60 votes","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"to end .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"There ' s virtually no chance","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"Republicans can expand their 54 to 46 majority in the Senate to 60 to 40 .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"If a Democrat wins the presidency ,","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"Republicans are still likely to keep the House , if not the Senate , too ,","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"leaving Washington as gridlocked as ever .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"Either way , Republican or Democratic ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"the new president ' s legal advisers will surely be put through their paces","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"to find ways","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"to circumvent Congress","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"and get things done .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"Obama has shown","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"that after one round of executive action on a divisive topic ,","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"and after saying","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"he ' s done everything","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"he can ,","depth":14},{"id":79,"text":"he ' s willing to send his advisers back","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"to interpret the laws even more permissively","depth":14},{"id":81,"text":"to allow them more leeway","depth":15},{"id":82,"text":"to come up with new ideas for action .","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"The best example is immigration .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"In November 2013 ,","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"when Obama was interrupted by a heckler in San Francisco","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"who demanded","depth":15},{"id":87,"text":"he stop all deportations ,","depth":15},{"id":88,"text":"the president insisted","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"he had done everything","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"he could .","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"His action","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"to defer deportation for young illegal immigrants","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"was the best","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"he could do","depth":16},{"id":95,"text":"without congressional action ,","depth":16},{"id":96,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"`` We 've got this Constitution ,","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"we 've got this whole thing about separation of powers , ''","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"Obama said .","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"`` So there is no shortcut to politics ,","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"and there 's no shortcut to democracy . ''","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"By November 2014 , Obama had changed his tune ,","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"and announced a plan","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"to defer deportation for an additional 4 million people .","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"That initiative , on hold","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"while under court challenge ,","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"would apply to 3.7 million undocumented parents of US citizens and legal permanent residents , plus another 300,000 young illegal immigrants","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"brought to the US as children .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"Democratic front-runner Hillary Clinton has pledged to go even further on immigration via executive action","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"if elected .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"On gun control , after the Sandy Hook massacre of December 2012 , Obama tried a two-track approach :","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"executive action and legislation .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"Vice President Joe Biden led an interagency task force","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"to come up with measures","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"the president could take on his own ;","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"one month after the massacre , Obama signed 23 executive actions","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"related to gun control .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"The effort in Congress was less fruitful ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"as a bipartisan bill","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"to expand background checks on gun buyers","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"and ban assault weapons","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"failed .","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"Until recently , Obama insisted","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"he ' d done everything","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"he could","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"on his own on guns .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"Massacres in Charleston , S.C. , Roseburg , Ore. , and San Bernardino , Calif.","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"- the last one at the hands of a radicalized Muslim couple -","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"have kept gun violence and domestic terrorism in the headlines ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"as have the daily statistics on gun deaths around the country .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"To Obama , gun violence isn ' t just a legal matter ,","depth":4},{"id":132,"text":"it ' s a moral issue and one of the scourges of our times .","depth":4},{"id":133,"text":"He has made clear","depth":5},{"id":134,"text":"that in his remaining time as president , keeping guns out of the \" wrong hands \" is a top priority .","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"Though most of the recent , high-profile gun incidents have involved weapons","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"that were legally obtained ,","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"Obama seems undeterred .","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"\" What I asked my team to do is to see what more we could do","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"to strengthen our enforcement","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"and prevent guns from falling into the wrong hands ,","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"to make sure","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"that criminals , people","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"who are mentally unstable ,","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"and those","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"who could pose a danger to themselves or others","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"are less likely to get a gun , \"","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"Obama told reporters Monday after a meeting with Justice Department officials in the Oval Office .","depth":6},{"id":148,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":149,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":150,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":151,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":152,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":153,"text":"Obama said","depth":4},{"id":154,"text":"his team made recommendations","depth":5},{"id":155,"text":"that are \" well within my legal authority and the executive branch , \"","depth":6},{"id":156,"text":"and also \" ones","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"that the overwhelming majority of the American people ,","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"including gun owners ,","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"support and believe in . \"","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"Polls show","depth":6},{"id":161,"text":"expanded background checks have strong public support ,","depth":6},{"id":162,"text":"though in the wake of San Bernardino , a majority of Americans now oppose a ban on assault weapons ,","depth":5},{"id":163,"text":"according to the latest ABC News/Washington Post poll .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":327,